Hello Tom,

You could add a custom RegexRule to your canonicalizationPolicy, something like this:

      &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.canonicalize.RegexRule&quot;&gt;
       &lt;property name=&quot;regex&quot; value=&quot;(.*)XTCsid=[a-zA-Z0-9]+(.*)&quot; /&gt;
       &lt;property name=&quot;format&quot; value=&quot;$1$2&quot; /&gt;
      &lt;/bean&gt;

(You will probably want to fine-tune this rule for your use case.) The regex needs to match the full url, and the parts of the url that you want to retain in the canonicalized version, you need to do explicitly with capturing groups ($1, $2 etc), as in the example above.

